This is the error I'm talking about:
https://logs.onap.org/production/vex-yul-ecomp-jenkins-1/sdc-master-csit-uiSanity-testng/1195/screenshots/addPmDictionaryDeploymentArtifactToPnfAndCheckMagnifierTest-36b3b0448a8a.png

I'm sorry, but I'm not the author of the original code, so I don't know how this class is being used. But I'm fixing an introduced bug, that was caused because the default constructor was removed.
I reproduced the error again and it fails during a call to the endpoint "org.openecomp.sdc.be.servlets.GenericArtifactBrowserServlet.searchFor" which receives a payload of type GenericArtifactQueryInfo:

public Response searchFor(
        @Parameter(description = "Generic Artifact search model", required = true) GenericArtifactQueryInfo query,
        @Context final HttpServletRequest request)

So I believe the binding in that endpoint fails, giving a 400 Bad Request with message:
"Cannot construct instance of `org.openecomp.sdc.be.info.GenericArtifactQueryInfo` (no Creators, like default construct, exist): cannot deserialize from Object value (no delegate- or property-based Creator)
 at [Source: (org.glassfish.jersey.message.internal.ReaderInterceptorExecutor$UnCloseableInputStream); line: 1, column: 2]".
